___________________________________________________

Incorporating the genres into the model was actually super important. Before adding these features as separate columns, I was getting very similar recommendations for every title I searched, probably because the model was mostly weighted towards using titles that were popular overall and rated mostly between 7-9 out of 10. In other words, the data that I gave the model was not that different for each title until I included more genre information.

benchmark = []
# Iterate over all algorithms
for algorithm in [SVD(), NMF(), KNNBasic(), KNNWithMeans(), KNNWithZScore(), BaselineOnly()]:
    # Perform cross validation
    results = cross_validate(algorithm, data, measures=['RMSE'], cv=5, verbose=False)
    
    # Get results & append algorithm name
    tmp = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(results).mean(axis=0)
    tmp = tmp.append(pd.Series([str(algorithm).split(' ')[0].split('.')[-1]], index=['Algorithm']))
    benchmark.append(tmp)
